name: Fan Rotom
flavorText: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
Ability1Text: If you have 9 or more Pokemon Tool cards in your discard pile, ignore all Energy in the attack cost of each of this Pokemon's attacks.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Shaymin
flavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Yungoos
flavorText: It wanders around in a never-ending search for food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustion and falls asleep on the spot.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Gumshoos
flavorText: It adores having Rattata and Raticate for dinner, but as it's diurnal, it never encounters them. This Pokemon boasts incredible patience.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. If you find a Pokemon there, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Oranguru
flavorText: Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokemon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.
Attack1Text: Put 3 cards from your discard pile on the bottom of your deck in any order.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Type: Null
flavorText: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokemon has some hidden special power.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Silvally-GX
Ability1Text: Your Basic Pokemon in play have no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Drampa
flavorText: This Pokemon is friendly to people and loves children most of all. It comes from deep in the mountains to play with children it likes in town.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

name: Leafeon-GX
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 50 damage from 1 of your Pokemon that has any Energy attached to it.
Attack2Text: For each of your Benched Basic Pokemon, search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokemon and put it onto that Pokemon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Pheromosa-GX
Attack1Text: If you go first, you can use this attack on your first turn.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Glaceon-GX
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, your opponent's Pokemon-GX and Pokemon-EX in play, in their hand, and in their discard pile have no Abilities, except for Freezing Gaze.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Xurkitree-GX
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon that have any Special Energy attached to them.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Add a card you find there to their Prize cards face down. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Dawn Wings Necrozma-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent. Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon during your opponent's next turn. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Celesteela-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.

name: Dusk Mane Necrozma-GX
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Dialga-GX
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Palkia-GX
Attack1Text: Move any number of Energy from your Benched Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Lunala-GX
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Psychic Energy from 1 of your Pokemon to another of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't be healed during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Knock Out 1 of your opponent's Basic Pokemon that isn't a Pokemon-GX. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)
